WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:32.583 --> 00:00:34.666
- Did it hurt her?
- What?

3
00:00:34.750 --> 00:00:36.250
No. Not at all.

4
00:00:36.875 --> 00:00:40.375
She never cries. She doesn’t even
wake up when I change her. Hm?

5
00:00:41.041 --> 00:00:42.916
You know. it doesn’t hurt her.

6
00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:44.583
It hurts you though.

7
00:00:45.083 --> 00:00:46.250
You’re ashamed of her.

8
00:00:46.791 --> 00:00:48.000
My daughter…

9
00:00:48.083 --> 00:00:49.166
{\an8}PAMPLONA. NOVEMBER 1973

10
00:00:49.250 --> 00:00:51.625
{\an8}Mmm. You’re so beautiful.

11
00:00:54.708 --> 00:00:57.458
If you helped me give her a bath
and held her in your arms.

12
00:00:57.541 --> 00:00:59.083
you’d be over this nonsense.

13
00:00:59.166 --> 00:01:01.000
Look at her. Look.

14
00:01:01.083 --> 00:01:02.541
She’s such a darling.

15
00:01:03.458 --> 00:01:05.458
I don’t want her like theirs.

16
00:01:06.541 --> 00:01:08.166
You don’t know what their lives were like.

17
00:01:08.250 --> 00:01:10.458
It’s been 40 years
since you’ve seen either of them.

18
00:01:10.541 --> 00:01:12.416
What do you know about anyone’s life?

19
00:01:13.083 --> 00:01:15.458
But I know what her life will be like.

20
00:01:19.750 --> 00:01:21.666
Wherever her mother is.
she’ll have her home.

21
00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:24.000
What are we going to do?

22
00:01:24.083 --> 00:01:26.500
We’ll follow the doctor’s recommendations

23
00:01:27.125 --> 00:01:28.583
as soon as we can.

24
00:01:29.458 --> 00:01:31.125
She’ll never know about it.

25
00:01:31.750 --> 00:01:33.958
No one will ever know.

26
00:01:34.791 --> 00:01:37.666
She’ll have a normal life.
Perfectly normal.

27
00:01:38.250 --> 00:01:40.458
You’re going to stop being so squeamish.

28
00:01:40.541 --> 00:01:44.000
You’re going to love your daughter
and start behaving like a real father.

29
00:01:44.083 --> 00:01:45.416
Will you be able to do that?

30
00:01:45.500 --> 00:01:46.916
I already love her.

31
00:01:51.291 --> 00:01:53.375
And I’ll do whatever I have to.

32
00:01:53.458 --> 00:01:55.416
I’ll do anything for you. my love.

33
00:01:58.458 --> 00:02:00.625
Your mother will always be here for you.

34
00:02:02.166 --> 00:02:03.375
Always…

35
00:02:05.750 --> 00:02:11.250
{\an8}MY DEAREST SEÑORITA

36
00:02:27.875 --> 00:02:29.583
- Hello. Miss!
- Hi. Miss!

37
00:02:30.125 --> 00:02:31.125
Hey!

38
00:02:39.500 --> 00:02:42.250
DE JUAN ANTIQUE SHOP

39
00:02:42.333 --> 00:02:46.083
PAMPLONA. DECEMBER 1999

40
00:02:46.166 --> 00:02:49.916
<i>“Our preaching is in vain.</i>
<i>and your faith is also in vain.”</i>

41
00:02:50.416 --> 00:02:54.166
This means that if Christ
hasn’t really risen from the dead.

42
00:02:54.250 --> 00:02:55.833
the Church must remain silent.

43
00:02:55.916 --> 00:02:56.750
Yes. Javier?

44
00:02:56.833 --> 00:02:59.041
But. miss. is clapping for the Pope
considered a sin?

45
00:02:59.125 --> 00:03:00.583
Not at all. my dear.

46
00:03:00.666 --> 00:03:03.041
But it’s not what we mean
by the fourth commandment. either.

47
00:03:03.125 --> 00:03:05.375
So it’s okay if I clap
when I see him on TV?

48
00:03:05.458 --> 00:03:07.083
’Cause I like him a lot.

49
00:03:07.166 --> 00:03:09.166
Yes. clap as much
as you feel like. Javier.

50
00:03:09.250 --> 00:03:10.666
But you’re not obliged to.

51
00:03:10.750 --> 00:03:14.583
Keep in mind that the commandments
are obligations for all of us Catholics.

52
00:03:14.666 --> 00:03:15.833
Okay. I was worried.

53
00:03:15.916 --> 00:03:17.541
Thank you very much. miss.

54
00:03:17.625 --> 00:03:20.250
Well. you don’t need to worry
and we’re at the end of class.

55
00:03:20.333 --> 00:03:22.333
Remember to practice
your parts for the carols.

56
00:03:22.416 --> 00:03:23.250
The show is soon.

57
00:03:23.333 --> 00:03:25.333
- And leave the room tidy. please.
- Bye. miss!

58
00:03:25.416 --> 00:03:28.041
<i>We have breaking news</i>
<i>on the Wanninkhof case.</i>

59
00:03:28.125 --> 00:03:30.916
<i>In an exclusive interview</i>
<i>with a reporter from this station.</i>

60
00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:33.916
<i>family members maintain that</i>
<i>whoever killed the 19-year-old girl</i>

61
00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:36.291
<i>must have been someone</i>
<i>close to the victim.</i>

62
00:03:36.916 --> 00:03:39.500
Yeah. they say
it’s the mother’s best friend.

63
00:03:39.583 --> 00:03:41.666
the one with short hair
and a face like a pitbull.

64
00:03:41.750 --> 00:03:44.375
Grandma. that’s just people gossiping.

65
00:03:44.458 --> 00:03:45.833
- Hm.
- How can you say that?

66
00:03:45.916 --> 00:03:48.250
Well. I’m not saying
she’s guilty for sure.

67
00:03:48.333 --> 00:03:50.500
but she’s making things worse
for herself. isn’t she?

68
00:03:50.583 --> 00:03:53.833
That frown she always puts on her face.
it makes your blood run cold.

69
00:03:54.375 --> 00:03:56.041
And she’s not very ladylike.

70
00:03:56.125 --> 00:03:58.000
But Grandma. couldn’t you
say the same about me?

71
00:03:58.083 --> 00:04:00.625
I’m not exactly the most
ladylike person either.

72
00:04:01.125 --> 00:04:02.791
That family is already suffering enough

73
00:04:02.875 --> 00:04:05.208
without having to worry about
a killer living with them.

74
00:04:05.291 --> 00:04:07.958
There’s no way
you look like that woman. Come on!

75
00:04:08.041 --> 00:04:10.250
I’ve never heard such a load of nonsense.

76
00:04:10.333 --> 00:04:13.041
You have such a nice clean face.
the face of an angel.

77
00:04:13.125 --> 00:04:14.291
So that’s it!

78
00:04:14.375 --> 00:04:18.000
We’re just supposed to send all the ugly.
unfriendly. unladylike women to jail.

79
00:04:18.083 --> 00:04:19.125
Is that it?

80
00:04:19.208 --> 00:04:21.125
Until we run out of-- Ah!

81
00:04:22.958 --> 00:04:25.208
Grandma? Grandma? Grandma?

82
00:04:25.291 --> 00:04:26.291
Grandma?

83
00:04:27.541 --> 00:04:28.916
Hold on. I’m coming.

84
00:04:31.291 --> 00:04:34.291
Adela. sweetie… What happened?

85
00:04:39.708 --> 00:04:42.500
Grandma. don’t move. okay? I’ll get help.

86
00:04:42.583 --> 00:04:47.041
Just great.
And it had to be you. didn’t it. Adela?

87
00:04:47.125 --> 00:04:48.083
- Here we are.
- I’m sorry.

88
00:04:48.166 --> 00:04:50.916
For God’s sake. look at my car!
You pushed me right onto the sidewalk!

89
00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:52.500
- I’m really sorry. I--
- Snap out of it!

90
00:04:52.583 --> 00:04:54.083
Look at my car. You see that?

91
00:04:54.166 --> 00:04:55.750
You see the damage you caused?

92
00:04:55.833 --> 00:04:58.958
I’m terribly sorry. Begoña. I got
distracted talking to my grandma.

93
00:04:59.041 --> 00:05:01.583
Your grandma’s with you in the car?
Are you serious?

94
00:05:01.666 --> 00:05:03.958
I’m gonna call my brother
because I’m a nervous wreck now.

95
00:05:04.541 --> 00:05:06.375
- Thanks to you!
- Hello.

96
00:05:06.458 --> 00:05:08.041
We’ve just had an accident.

97
00:05:09.708 --> 00:05:12.541
On Duque de Ahumada.
close to Cortes de Navarra.

98
00:05:12.625 --> 00:05:13.958
An elderly lady.

99
00:05:14.666 --> 00:05:16.083
Please come quickly.

100
00:05:27.750 --> 00:05:29.708
Hello? Can you hear me?

101
00:05:29.791 --> 00:05:30.916
Are you okay?

102
00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:33.791
Yes. I’m fine. Is my grandmother okay?

103
00:05:33.875 --> 00:05:35.541
Don’t worry. we’re looking after her now.

104
00:05:35.625 --> 00:05:36.916
Let me take a look at you.

105
00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:39.958
I said I’m fine! Leave me alone. please.

106
00:05:40.041 --> 00:05:42.458
You won’t let me check you.
so it’s your responsibility

107
00:05:42.541 --> 00:05:44.541
if there’s anything wrong. okay?

108
00:05:45.250 --> 00:05:46.125
Grandma?

109
00:05:47.250 --> 00:05:50.291
The police will take me to the hospital
right behind the ambulance. okay?

110
00:05:50.375 --> 00:05:52.791
- I’ll be there with you.
- Yes. dear. Yes. Yes.

111
00:05:52.875 --> 00:05:55.875
Don’t worry. Adelina.
I’ll go with your granddaughter.

112
00:06:02.375 --> 00:06:04.708
FLEUR JAEGGY
SWEET DAYS OF DISCIPLINE

113
00:06:09.291 --> 00:06:11.750
<i>Attention please. paging Dr. Gonzales.</i>

114
00:06:11.833 --> 00:06:13.625
<i>You are needed</i>
<i>in the surgical ward. unit 4.</i>

115
00:06:13.708 --> 00:06:14.875
I didn’t know you were back.

116
00:06:15.625 --> 00:06:17.166
Since September.

117
00:06:17.250 --> 00:06:19.041
I know I should have come by to say hello.

118
00:06:19.541 --> 00:06:21.375
but I’ve been practically buried alive.

119
00:06:21.458 --> 00:06:24.791
My father is giving me
control of the company

120
00:06:25.291 --> 00:06:26.791
and I’ve been trying to catch up.

121
00:06:27.708 --> 00:06:29.916
So you’re not going back to London?

122
00:06:31.541 --> 00:06:33.166
I would have stayed in a heartbeat.

123
00:06:34.750 --> 00:06:36.750
But I always knew
it would turn out like this.

124
00:06:37.791 --> 00:06:40.208
I was hoping that my father.
the workaholic.

125
00:06:40.291 --> 00:06:43.041
would put off retiring.
or not retire at all.

126
00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:45.166
But no.

127
00:06:47.458 --> 00:06:48.791
How was your life there?

128
00:06:48.875 --> 00:06:50.583
Were you happy?

129
00:06:50.666 --> 00:06:51.583
Yes.

130
00:06:52.750 --> 00:06:54.708
It’s a city that goes on forever.

131
00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:59.166
Not to say anything against Pamplona
or the life we have here.

132
00:06:59.708 --> 00:07:02.625
but the truth is our Pamplona.
your world and mine.

133
00:07:03.125 --> 00:07:04.250
is very small.

134
00:07:04.750 --> 00:07:08.250
We don’t see more than ten streets
and a hundred people.

135
00:07:09.166 --> 00:07:11.541
And then. of course. you get to London.

136
00:07:12.791 --> 00:07:14.166
and the world is enormous.

137
00:07:15.416 --> 00:07:16.833
Then you have to come back.

138
00:07:18.708 --> 00:07:20.041
Then you have to come back.

139
00:07:22.541 --> 00:07:25.250
All right. Adelina. make sure
you do what the doctor told you.

140
00:07:25.333 --> 00:07:27.125
Go for walks. but slowly.

141
00:07:27.208 --> 00:07:28.625
and always have someone with you.

142
00:07:28.708 --> 00:07:29.583
Oh. my granddaughter!

143
00:07:29.666 --> 00:07:31.166
Oh. I see. She’s so tall and pretty.

144
00:07:31.250 --> 00:07:33.166
Well. then. off you go with her.

145
00:07:50.166 --> 00:07:51.291
Where have you been?

146
00:07:53.791 --> 00:07:54.833
Good evening.

147
00:07:55.416 --> 00:07:56.458
Did Grandma get back okay?

148
00:07:56.541 --> 00:07:58.333
I asked you where you were. Adela.

149
00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:01.083
I decided to walk back.

150
00:08:01.166 --> 00:08:02.833
And you just left your grandma?

151
00:08:04.208 --> 00:08:08.125
Dad. everything’s fine. I was a little
agitated and wanted to get some air.

152
00:08:08.208 --> 00:08:09.166
It’s no big deal.

153
00:08:09.250 --> 00:08:12.208
You young people think you can do
whatever you want. take no responsibility.

154
00:08:12.291 --> 00:08:14.708
- You don’t worry at all.
- Adela. your father is right.

155
00:08:14.791 --> 00:08:17.833
The responsible thing was
for you to come straight home.

156
00:08:18.375 --> 00:08:21.000
I just took a little walk. I’m sorry.

157
00:08:22.708 --> 00:08:24.916
There’s some dinner ready.
Heat it up for yourself.

158
00:08:25.416 --> 00:08:27.291
And let’s not dwell on this.
What’s done is done.

159
00:08:27.375 --> 00:08:30.250
<i>…emergency committees</i>
<i>have been set up for every local branch</i>

160
00:08:30.333 --> 00:08:32.708
<i>of the federal government</i>
<i>and every public sector office.</i>

161
00:08:32.791 --> 00:08:36.125
<i>but we must approach the dreaded prospect</i>
<i>of the Y2K bug calmly.</i>

162
00:08:36.208 --> 00:08:37.875
<i>The most important thing is not to panic.</i>

163
00:09:30.458 --> 00:09:32.833
Hey. they’re ringing the doorbell.
Can someone get it?

164
00:09:39.583 --> 00:09:41.833
Hi there. I’m Isabel Goñi.
the physiotherapist.

165
00:09:41.916 --> 00:09:43.791
I’m here to see Adelina Arrán.

166
00:09:43.875 --> 00:09:45.666
- Yes. this is… This is it. Come in.
- May I?

167
00:09:47.083 --> 00:09:48.166
Okay.

168
00:09:48.250 --> 00:09:51.375
God. this gets heavier every day.
Like hauling a corpse around.

169
00:09:54.833 --> 00:09:57.083
- And you are?
- Adela. I’m sorry.

170
00:09:57.166 --> 00:09:58.500
Nice to meet you.

171
00:10:00.875 --> 00:10:02.000
It’s that way.

172
00:10:02.083 --> 00:10:04.125
Down there? Let me just…

173
00:10:05.041 --> 00:10:07.041
Sorry it took us
so long to come to the door.

174
00:10:07.125 --> 00:10:08.333
No. don’t worry about it.

175
00:10:08.416 --> 00:10:09.833
And my coat? Where do I leave it?

176
00:10:09.916 --> 00:10:11.708
- I’ll put it here for you.
- Here?

177
00:10:12.416 --> 00:10:13.916
I’m Isabel. Pleased to meet you.

178
00:10:14.000 --> 00:10:15.041
Yes.

179
00:10:15.708 --> 00:10:18.291
- Come this way. if you’d be so kind.
- Sure. I’ll just take this off.

180
00:10:18.375 --> 00:10:21.041
Sweetie. could you grab my bag
from the floor there. please?

181
00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:25.000
Adelina. here’s the physiotherapist.
Her name is Isabel.

182
00:10:25.500 --> 00:10:27.500
Oh my goodness. Adelina.
you’re still in bed?

183
00:10:27.583 --> 00:10:31.083
As soon as I’m done setting up the table.
we’ll get you out of there.

184
00:10:31.166 --> 00:10:33.708
Because it’s not good to
be lying down all day.

185
00:10:34.250 --> 00:10:37.250
I should think I ought to rest
after the accident.

186
00:10:37.333 --> 00:10:39.083
I’m 88 years old. dear.

187
00:10:39.166 --> 00:10:40.333
Well. that’s exactly my point.

188
00:10:40.416 --> 00:10:42.750
If the doctor didn’t tell you
to stay in bed. don’t do it.

189
00:10:42.833 --> 00:10:44.791
Our bodies are very lazy.
they like to do nothing.

190
00:10:44.875 --> 00:10:45.708
Oh…

191
00:10:45.791 --> 00:10:47.958
Come on. let’s get up like this.
Hold onto me.

192
00:10:48.041 --> 00:10:49.875
Up we go. Adelina!

193
00:10:49.958 --> 00:10:51.666
On your side like that. Very good.

194
00:10:52.958 --> 00:10:56.250
Ugh. no. Every year
I feel less interested in the whole thing.

195
00:10:56.750 --> 00:10:59.083
And then the amount of food involved.

196
00:10:59.166 --> 00:11:01.500
you know. it makes me sick already.
to be honest.

197
00:11:02.125 --> 00:11:03.125
Hm?

198
00:11:03.666 --> 00:11:05.916
Yes. Yes. that’s right.
She’s starting today.

199
00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:06.916
Let’s see how it goes.

200
00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:09.541
That’s a traveling dress. huh?
That’s a new one for me.

201
00:11:09.625 --> 00:11:13.166
Well. getting married
in white wasn’t the thing back then.

202
00:11:13.250 --> 00:11:14.333
Yes. that’s right.

203
00:11:14.416 --> 00:11:18.375
Besides. my grandfather had died
a few weeks before the wedding. Hm.

204
00:11:18.458 --> 00:11:21.291
- So I wore black. but I was still elegant.
- Of course.

205
00:11:21.375 --> 00:11:23.416
In my cute little traveling dress.

206
00:11:23.500 --> 00:11:26.416
Adelina. turn your head this way now.
like before. that’s it.

207
00:11:26.500 --> 00:11:28.166
Push. push. push. Does it hurt?

208
00:11:28.250 --> 00:11:30.250
- No. No. no. No pain at all.
- No?

209
00:11:30.333 --> 00:11:31.291
Very good.

210
00:11:31.375 --> 00:11:33.083
Well. you looked very pretty.

211
00:11:33.166 --> 00:11:35.541
A real beauty. Okay. we’re all done here.

212
00:11:35.625 --> 00:11:37.125
Let me get that slipper.

213
00:11:38.666 --> 00:11:39.875
Shall I tell you how it went?

214
00:11:39.958 --> 00:11:42.791
Uh. hold on. I’ll get my mother.
She’ll want to hear it.

215
00:11:43.500 --> 00:11:45.500
- Okay then. hold onto me.
- Mom?

216
00:11:45.583 --> 00:11:48.458
Oh. that felt wonderful. my dear!

217
00:11:48.541 --> 00:11:49.875
- It did?
- Oh!

218
00:11:49.958 --> 00:11:52.583
- I’m glad!
- Your hands know just what to do. Isabel!

219
00:11:52.666 --> 00:11:53.958
- Well…
- Have you finished?

220
00:11:54.041 --> 00:11:56.000
Yes. all done. She’s fine.

221
00:11:56.083 --> 00:11:58.458
There’s tension.
which is a normal response.

222
00:11:58.541 --> 00:12:00.875
I think the sessions
we have planned should be enough.

223
00:12:01.375 --> 00:12:03.833
Still. she needs to be more active.

224
00:12:03.916 --> 00:12:07.166
Go up and down the stairs.
walk a bit. that type of thing.

225
00:12:07.250 --> 00:12:09.166
This girl wants
to put me in a green tracksuit

226
00:12:09.250 --> 00:12:11.375
and take me to a ballroom
to do the foxtrot.

227
00:12:11.458 --> 00:12:12.791
like those old folks in Madrid.

228
00:12:13.416 --> 00:12:15.750
Well. thank you.
We’ll make sure she moves a bit more.

229
00:12:15.833 --> 00:12:18.208
- Great.
- I’ll move more when I’m good and ready.

230
00:12:18.291 --> 00:12:19.958
Not a minute earlier.

231
00:12:20.750 --> 00:12:23.000
- And how are you feeling. sweetie?
- Good.

232
00:12:23.083 --> 00:12:25.500
You were driving. right?
Has that been looked at?

233
00:12:25.583 --> 00:12:27.333
Uh. no. I was just touching my neck.

234
00:12:27.416 --> 00:12:29.666
Touching your neck ’cause you’re in pain.

235
00:12:29.750 --> 00:12:30.666
Lemme see.

236
00:12:30.750 --> 00:12:33.125
Uh… No. but. I’m fine.
really. It’s nothing.

237
00:12:33.750 --> 00:12:36.041
Oof. yeah. You’re really tense.

238
00:12:36.583 --> 00:12:38.291
Do you want me to take a quick look at it?

239
00:12:38.375 --> 00:12:39.958
Let her take a look. okay?

240
00:12:40.583 --> 00:12:41.666
Do it for me.

241
00:12:42.166 --> 00:12:44.208
Your mother and I will
be in the living room.

242
00:12:44.291 --> 00:12:45.333
Come on. Cruz.

243
00:12:45.416 --> 00:12:46.458
Come.

244
00:12:46.958 --> 00:12:48.666
Unbutton your cardigan if you like.

245
00:12:55.458 --> 00:12:59.000
Sit with your legs pointing outwards
and uncover your shoulders.

246
00:13:06.875 --> 00:13:09.791
- It was this side. right?
- Yes. yes.

247
00:13:10.666 --> 00:13:11.708
Let’s see.

248
00:13:14.375 --> 00:13:16.500
I need you to lower it a little more.

249
00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:18.125
Undo one more button.

250
00:13:19.041 --> 00:13:20.208
That’s fine.

251
00:13:21.041 --> 00:13:22.083
Okay.

252
00:13:25.958 --> 00:13:28.833
I’ll examine you now.
and if it hurts. let me know.

253
00:13:29.625 --> 00:13:31.291
And tell me how intense it is.

254
00:13:32.083 --> 00:13:33.500
Now turn your head.

255
00:13:35.208 --> 00:13:36.375
How’s that feel?

256
00:13:36.458 --> 00:13:38.000
It’s tense. but it doesn’t hurt.

257
00:13:38.083 --> 00:13:39.166
Very good.

258
00:13:49.416 --> 00:13:50.375
Oh!

259
00:13:51.166 --> 00:13:52.291
What’s wrong?

260
00:13:52.375 --> 00:13:54.541
Here. here you go. Did I hurt you?

261
00:13:54.625 --> 00:13:56.041
Are you okay?

262
00:14:16.875 --> 00:14:21.500
<i>That lost stare into nothing</i>
<i>Looking for the same thing as you </i>

263
00:14:21.583 --> 00:14:25.166
<i>To learn something in life </i>

264
00:14:25.250 --> 00:14:28.708
<i>To understand love </i>

265
00:14:28.791 --> 00:14:32.416
<i>To discover what the world is like </i>

266
00:14:32.500 --> 00:14:34.208
<i>To understand </i>

267
00:14:36.083 --> 00:14:39.875
<i>To learn something in life </i>

268
00:14:39.958 --> 00:14:43.125
<i>To understand love completely </i>

269
00:14:45.250 --> 00:14:47.791
<i>A dream come true </i>

270
00:14:58.916 --> 00:15:00.666
Come in! Really. come on in.

271
00:15:00.750 --> 00:15:03.083
I just came over to say hi.
I have to be getting to work.

272
00:15:03.166 --> 00:15:05.833
Okay. No. hold on a sec.
Sorry. I-I can’t hear you.

273
00:15:08.291 --> 00:15:09.875
Whenever I listen to Monica Naranjo.

274
00:15:09.958 --> 00:15:12.208
I’m just transported. she’s so great.
You were saying?

275
00:15:12.291 --> 00:15:14.291
That I just came
to say hi to you. I’m on my way.

276
00:15:14.375 --> 00:15:17.291
Okay. but sit for a few minutes
and have a beer with me. honey.

277
00:15:17.375 --> 00:15:19.375
Another day. I haven’t eaten anything yet.

278
00:15:19.458 --> 00:15:21.666
Don’t worry. beer is
full of carbohydrates.

279
00:15:22.708 --> 00:15:24.041
It’s like a meal in a can.

280
00:15:24.125 --> 00:15:26.000
All right. thank you. But only one.

281
00:15:26.708 --> 00:15:27.750
Cheers!

282
00:15:29.208 --> 00:15:30.958
Mmm! Oh. that’s good!

283
00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:33.916
- So. how are you?
- Fine.

284
00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:35.500
I heard you had an accident.

285
00:15:36.958 --> 00:15:38.583
It was just a little scare.

286
00:15:38.666 --> 00:15:41.625
You ran into Begoña. right?
Her father is Gómez Arellano.

287
00:15:41.708 --> 00:15:44.000
Yeah. she went ballistic on me.

288
00:15:44.875 --> 00:15:46.125
She’s a bit of a dumbass.

289
00:15:47.041 --> 00:15:49.458
Fortunately. her brother
was there to handle things.

290
00:15:50.041 --> 00:15:52.958
- The one just back from London. right?
- Yes. Santi.

291
00:15:53.041 --> 00:15:54.541
Yeah. he’s a sweet guy.

292
00:15:54.625 --> 00:15:57.000
Well. every cloud has a silver lining.

293
00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:00.916
Do you have any plans for the holidays?

294
00:16:03.416 --> 00:16:05.791
You know the name
they called me in Pamplona all my life?

295
00:16:05.875 --> 00:16:06.875
I do.

296
00:16:06.958 --> 00:16:08.000
You do?

297
00:16:09.375 --> 00:16:10.375
Horse Girl.

298
00:16:10.458 --> 00:16:13.916
Those sons of bitches
aren’t very discreet. honey. are they?

299
00:16:14.458 --> 00:16:15.500
I just found out…

300
00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:19.625
that some people call me
“Our Mother José María.”

301
00:16:20.375 --> 00:16:22.250
- What?
- How do you like that. girl?

302
00:16:22.333 --> 00:16:23.458
You’ve gotta be kidding.

303
00:16:23.541 --> 00:16:24.583
So there we are.

304
00:16:25.416 --> 00:16:27.583
We’re still living in the 16th century.

305
00:16:28.083 --> 00:16:32.416
This is a society where people are still
scared of tall women and effeminate men.

306
00:16:32.500 --> 00:16:35.500
I have to forgive them because.
well. I’m a priest.

307
00:16:35.583 --> 00:16:36.541
But you don’t.

308
00:16:38.125 --> 00:16:39.791
Not everybody is like that.

309
00:16:40.416 --> 00:16:41.458
Oh. really?

310
00:16:42.083 --> 00:16:44.541
There are people here in Pamplona
who might surprise you.

311
00:16:44.625 --> 00:16:45.625
in a good way.

312
00:16:46.750 --> 00:16:49.291
Well. you really must tell
Our Mother José María

313
00:16:49.375 --> 00:16:50.916
who those people are. okay?

314
00:16:51.000 --> 00:16:51.875
I promise you.

315
00:16:52.500 --> 00:16:54.583
But some other day. I should get going.

316
00:16:55.166 --> 00:16:57.041
How mysterious. I like it.

317
00:16:57.125 --> 00:16:58.666
She’s got style. this one.

318
00:16:59.333 --> 00:17:00.708
Thanks a lot for the beer.

319
00:17:00.791 --> 00:17:01.750
Hm.

320
00:17:02.750 --> 00:17:05.500
Yes. Mr. Gómez-Arellano is away next week.

321
00:17:07.041 --> 00:17:09.166
Call me tomorrow
and we’ll arrange something.

322
00:17:10.000 --> 00:17:11.125
Have a good day.

323
00:17:12.166 --> 00:17:14.541
Mamen. can you get me those
forms I asked for. please?

324
00:17:14.625 --> 00:17:15.625
Yes.

325
00:17:16.208 --> 00:17:18.416
Adela. how nice! What brings you here?

326
00:17:18.500 --> 00:17:21.041
I’ve been working
at my father’s antique shop

327
00:17:21.125 --> 00:17:23.000
and earning a salary for four years.

328
00:17:23.083 --> 00:17:24.958
And I’ve spent almost no money.

329
00:17:25.458 --> 00:17:27.708
- I want to do something with it.
- Good plan.

330
00:17:27.791 --> 00:17:30.250
It’s silly to leave
your money there doing nothing.

331
00:17:30.333 --> 00:17:32.166
How much are we talking about?

332
00:17:32.250 --> 00:17:33.791
About six million pesetas.

333
00:17:33.875 --> 00:17:34.833
Uh-huh.

334
00:17:35.500 --> 00:17:36.541
That’s very good.

335
00:17:36.625 --> 00:17:39.583
Have you considered real estate?
A down payment on a condo?

336
00:17:39.666 --> 00:17:40.625
No. nothing.

337
00:17:41.958 --> 00:17:43.000
Okay.

338
00:17:44.625 --> 00:17:45.958
How much risk can you live with?

339
00:17:46.041 --> 00:17:47.625
As little as possible.

340
00:17:47.708 --> 00:17:48.750
All right.

341
00:17:49.333 --> 00:17:51.666
I’d suggest government bonds.

342
00:17:51.750 --> 00:17:53.708
Low interest. very safe.

343
00:17:53.791 --> 00:17:54.916
What do you think?

344
00:17:55.000 --> 00:17:55.958
Whatever you say.

345
00:17:56.041 --> 00:17:57.041
Okay.

346
00:17:58.000 --> 00:18:00.083
So we’ll do the paperwork.
you’ll come in to sign it.

347
00:18:00.166 --> 00:18:02.416
and you won’t have to
think about it after that.

348
00:18:02.916 --> 00:18:04.250
I’ll look after it.

349
00:18:06.916 --> 00:18:09.583
Oh. hi. I’m sorry.
I didn’t know you were here.

350
00:18:09.666 --> 00:18:11.333
I was just getting a glass of water.
May I?

351
00:18:11.416 --> 00:18:12.375
Sure. come in.

352
00:18:13.500 --> 00:18:15.958
- Uh…
- Oh. I’ll get it for you.

353
00:18:23.833 --> 00:18:24.916
Thanks.

354
00:18:35.541 --> 00:18:36.916
Uh. would you like a coffee?

355
00:18:37.416 --> 00:18:38.833
I was about to make a pot.

356
00:18:39.791 --> 00:18:43.166
If you don’t mind. I’d love a coffee.
I still have a lot of work to get through.

357
00:18:50.958 --> 00:18:52.541
Adela. listen. about the other day.

358
00:18:52.625 --> 00:18:53.708
I’m really sorry.

359
00:18:54.208 --> 00:18:57.250
I made you feel uncomfortable.
and I-I really didn’t mean to do that.

360
00:18:57.333 --> 00:19:00.208
- Forgive me.
- I’m not very good with physical contact.

361
00:19:00.708 --> 00:19:01.625
And…

362
00:19:02.291 --> 00:19:03.666
I’m sorry about how I reacted.

363
00:19:03.750 --> 00:19:07.375
No. I can come on way too fucking strong.
and I’m terrible with boundaries.

364
00:19:07.458 --> 00:19:09.625
You wanted to help me
and it was awkward. That was all.

365
00:19:12.416 --> 00:19:16.500
Okay. but. um. if you’d like me to check
that everything’s fine with you.

366
00:19:16.583 --> 00:19:18.041
just let me know.

367
00:19:18.125 --> 00:19:21.500
And we’ll find a way
to make sure you feel comfortable.

368
00:19:22.291 --> 00:19:25.000
I know I’m bad at respecting boundaries.
but I’m really good at my job.

369
00:19:25.083 --> 00:19:27.416
And one thing I hate is pain.
Yours and mine.

370
00:19:27.500 --> 00:19:29.541
- I’ll think about it. I promise.
- Okay.

371
00:19:29.625 --> 00:19:31.416
Hmm. Adela. please.
don’t you think it’s time

372
00:19:31.500 --> 00:19:33.750
to go down and help out your father?

373
00:19:36.083 --> 00:19:38.583
Will you continue with my mother-in-law
or have you finished?

374
00:19:40.416 --> 00:19:43.416
We’re done for the day.
I’ll just go pack up my things.

375
00:20:54.875 --> 00:20:55.875
Good.

376
00:20:57.333 --> 00:20:58.666
This arm’s all done.

377
00:21:16.416 --> 00:21:18.166
I’m heading out. sweetie.

378
00:21:18.250 --> 00:21:20.000
Yeah. I could hear you
coming down the hall.

379
00:21:20.083 --> 00:21:22.625
I bet you could. With this thing.
I sound like a garbage truck.

380
00:21:24.125 --> 00:21:25.166
So. um…

381
00:21:26.333 --> 00:21:30.083
Hey. the Casablanca video store.
do you know how to get there?

382
00:21:33.500 --> 00:21:35.500
We’re almost there. okay?
That’s my car on the left.

383
00:21:35.583 --> 00:21:37.708
Oh! <i>Fucking Åmål.</i>

384
00:21:37.791 --> 00:21:41.000
Wow! This movie is just fabulous.
It’s so weird.

385
00:21:41.625 --> 00:21:44.750
Imagine Fassbinder making
a movie for children. but with lesbians.

386
00:21:44.833 --> 00:21:46.750
I haven’t seen it. When did it come out?

387
00:21:46.833 --> 00:21:47.833
Just last year.

388
00:21:47.916 --> 00:21:49.791
Shit. I’d have saved myself a lot of drama

389
00:21:49.875 --> 00:21:51.958
if this flick
had been around ten years ago.

390
00:21:56.041 --> 00:21:57.916
So. what movie are we looking for exactly?

391
00:21:58.000 --> 00:21:59.750
Um. Carl Dreyer’s <i>Joan of Arc.</i>

392
00:21:59.833 --> 00:22:02.083
It’s a silent movie.
The poster is in black and white.

393
00:22:02.166 --> 00:22:04.916
and the actress has super short hair
and a crown made out of straw.

394
00:22:05.000 --> 00:22:06.916
and she’s crying.
She’s so pretty. beautiful.

395
00:22:07.000 --> 00:22:07.916
Maria Falconetti.

396
00:22:08.000 --> 00:22:10.125
Maria Falconetti. yes. that’s her!

397
00:22:10.208 --> 00:22:11.666
I couldn’t remember her name.

398
00:22:11.750 --> 00:22:13.666
I just love that movie. It drives me wild.

399
00:22:13.750 --> 00:22:16.583
It’s perfect.
It’s more than film. it’s like a prayer.

400
00:22:17.583 --> 00:22:18.666
Yeah. a prayer.

401
00:22:19.166 --> 00:22:20.208
You’re right.

402
00:22:20.708 --> 00:22:23.875
She has that powerful stare. you know?
With those eyes!

403
00:22:24.375 --> 00:22:27.458
It’s like you spend the whole movie
wanting to tell her you’re sorry.

404
00:22:27.541 --> 00:22:28.666
I get the shivers every time.

405
00:22:28.750 --> 00:22:31.083
It was back when everyone
was making big-budget epics.

406
00:22:31.166 --> 00:22:33.458
and Dreyer goes in
this whole other direction.

407
00:22:33.541 --> 00:22:34.916
It’s so spiritual.

408
00:22:35.000 --> 00:22:36.166
- Yes.
- So…

409
00:22:37.083 --> 00:22:38.500
- Theatrical.
- Theatrical.

410
00:22:38.583 --> 00:22:39.916
That’s totally it.

411
00:22:40.625 --> 00:22:43.500
You know what? I want you
to see the play I’m doing.

412
00:22:43.583 --> 00:22:45.458
- You do theater?
- Yes. I’m an actress.

413
00:22:45.541 --> 00:22:47.583
Although the physiotherapy
is how I make a living.

414
00:22:47.666 --> 00:22:49.750
and I’m really good at it. unfortunately.

415
00:22:49.833 --> 00:22:50.666
Mmm.

416
00:22:50.750 --> 00:22:53.333
I guess we all have our
own antique store. huh.

417
00:22:55.458 --> 00:22:57.291
So. where’s the play?

418
00:22:57.375 --> 00:23:00.041
It’s playing this Thursday night.
at the ENT.

419
00:23:00.125 --> 00:23:02.000
in the old part of town. you know it?

420
00:23:02.083 --> 00:23:03.958
We’re doing a version of <i>Joan of Arc.</i>

421
00:23:04.041 --> 00:23:05.000
I’ll be there.

422
00:23:05.083 --> 00:23:06.000
Oh wow!

423
00:23:06.083 --> 00:23:08.166
Okay. like. don’t expect
a big production or anything.

424
00:23:08.250 --> 00:23:10.083
It’s just a company
with some of my girlfriends.

425
00:23:10.166 --> 00:23:11.416
and I’m no Falconetti. you know.

426
00:23:11.500 --> 00:23:13.750
I hope not. I hope you talk. at least.

427
00:23:13.833 --> 00:23:16.041
Yeah. sure. That I can do.

428
00:23:17.041 --> 00:23:18.000
Well. then.

429
00:23:18.500 --> 00:23:20.125
It’s getting late. I should be going now.

430
00:23:20.208 --> 00:23:22.208
- Okay.
- Do you know your way back to the car?

431
00:23:22.291 --> 00:23:24.333
Sure. sure. I’ve got it. don’t worry.

432
00:23:38.500 --> 00:23:40.250
It’s a shame to cut it like this. Cruz.

433
00:23:40.333 --> 00:23:42.666
The best way to roast a piglet
is whole or in half.

434
00:23:42.750 --> 00:23:45.416
Mikel. you know very well
I can’t bear to see the animal’s face.

435
00:23:45.500 --> 00:23:47.583
Fine. as you wish.
You want pieces. pieces it is.

436
00:23:47.666 --> 00:23:49.375
- Yes. I’d like pieces.
- Here you go.

437
00:23:50.333 --> 00:23:52.375
- How much is it?
- 1.500 please.

438
00:23:52.458 --> 00:23:53.458
Here.

439
00:23:53.541 --> 00:23:54.583
Okay.

440
00:23:55.875 --> 00:23:57.500
See you. Happy holidays.

441
00:23:57.583 --> 00:24:00.166
- Same to you.
- Okay. we’re done. Let’s go home.

442
00:24:00.666 --> 00:24:02.041
Next. please. Who’s next?

443
00:24:06.791 --> 00:24:08.375
- Mom.
- What?

444
00:24:08.458 --> 00:24:09.916
I need to see a doctor.

445
00:24:11.833 --> 00:24:13.791
- Honey. are you okay?
- Yes.

446
00:24:13.875 --> 00:24:15.458
It’s something from the accident.

447
00:24:15.541 --> 00:24:17.916
Well. as soon as we get home.
I’ll call Dr. Etxebarría.

448
00:24:18.000 --> 00:24:19.125
I’ll go with you.

449
00:24:19.916 --> 00:24:22.416
No. there’s nothing wrong.
I just need a checkup.

450
00:24:22.500 --> 00:24:24.416
I mean. I want a checkup.

451
00:24:24.916 --> 00:24:26.333
But not with Dr. Etxebarría.

452
00:24:26.416 --> 00:24:27.666
That’s silly. Adela.

453
00:24:27.750 --> 00:24:30.541
He’s known you since you were born.
and he treats the family.

454
00:24:30.625 --> 00:24:32.708
Mom. with a gynecologist.

455
00:24:34.625 --> 00:24:36.291
- See you later.
- See you.

456
00:24:44.375 --> 00:24:46.250
Is there something I should know about?

457
00:24:47.125 --> 00:24:51.041
No. nothing. It’s just. I’m 26
and I’ve never had an exam.

458
00:24:51.125 --> 00:24:54.208
If you’ve never been it’s because
there’s no reason to go. silly.

459
00:24:54.291 --> 00:24:58.125
At 26. unless you have strange symptoms
you don’t need a checkup.

460
00:24:58.625 --> 00:24:59.916
- When you’re my age…
- Mom.

461
00:25:00.000 --> 00:25:02.541
I brought it up because
I want you to come with me.

462
00:25:02.625 --> 00:25:03.958
but I can go alone.

463
00:25:04.041 --> 00:25:05.708
Well. you don’t have to say it like that.

464
00:25:05.791 --> 00:25:07.291
I know you’re a grown woman.

465
00:25:07.375 --> 00:25:08.375
Mom.

466
00:25:08.875 --> 00:25:10.916
I’ve been taking estrogen since I was 15

467
00:25:11.000 --> 00:25:12.708
and all I know is that I need it.

468
00:25:13.291 --> 00:25:16.000
Well. yes. you need it for what you have.

469
00:25:16.083 --> 00:25:17.416
But what is it I have?

470
00:25:17.500 --> 00:25:19.583
I know I can’t have children.
I don’t get my period.

471
00:25:19.666 --> 00:25:21.541
and I need to take estrogen.
So what is all that?

472
00:25:21.625 --> 00:25:23.583
Oh. Adela. that’s all there is to it.

473
00:25:30.208 --> 00:25:32.541
Okay. we’ll talk after the big meal.

474
00:25:32.625 --> 00:25:35.166
And. Mom. listen to me. okay?
Don’t make so much food.

475
00:25:35.250 --> 00:25:37.083
Restrain yourself. okay?

476
00:25:39.208 --> 00:25:42.958
Put Auntie in charge. then.
There you go. that’s it. Okay. kisses.

477
00:25:46.333 --> 00:25:47.458
Keep stirring. keep stirring.

478
00:25:49.125 --> 00:25:50.083
José?

479
00:25:51.625 --> 00:25:53.625
Before you were a priest.

480
00:25:54.166 --> 00:25:55.416
were you ever in love?

481
00:25:57.625 --> 00:26:00.375
Honey. watch the bowl.
you’re gonna spill everything.

482
00:26:01.125 --> 00:26:02.250
Hang on.

483
00:26:02.333 --> 00:26:04.166
Pour it in. Go on. all of it.

484
00:26:05.083 --> 00:26:07.875
There. That’s perfect.
Here. give it a try.

485
00:26:09.500 --> 00:26:10.375
Mmm.

486
00:26:10.458 --> 00:26:11.416
Delicious.

487
00:26:11.500 --> 00:26:13.000
The potatoes are just right.

488
00:26:13.083 --> 00:26:14.833
We’ll give it a little time to rest.

489
00:26:14.916 --> 00:26:16.916
So come with me.
I have something to show you.

490
00:26:20.708 --> 00:26:21.875
<i>Hey!</i>

491
00:26:21.958 --> 00:26:23.583
Look.

492
00:26:24.250 --> 00:26:25.458
What is this?

493
00:26:26.750 --> 00:26:27.791
Wait…

494
00:26:28.708 --> 00:26:30.083
Here we go. right here.

495
00:26:30.166 --> 00:26:34.000
<i>Ah! Well. well. well!</i>
<i>What do we have here?</i>

496
00:26:35.000 --> 00:26:37.375
<i>- What is this?</i>
<i>- It’s just scandalous!</i>

497
00:26:37.458 --> 00:26:40.250
<i>It’s scandalous how gorgeous you are!</i>

498
00:26:40.916 --> 00:26:43.958
<i>Come here.</i>
<i>If you’re crazy. girl. call me up.</i>

499
00:26:44.041 --> 00:26:45.041
<i>If you’re not…</i>

500
00:26:45.125 --> 00:26:46.583
<i>It’s your loss. sweetheart!</i>

501
00:26:46.666 --> 00:26:47.791
<i>Ah!</i>

502
00:27:01.041 --> 00:27:02.333
His name was…

503
00:27:02.875 --> 00:27:03.791
Alonso.

504
00:27:05.333 --> 00:27:06.375
What happened to him?

505
00:27:07.166 --> 00:27:09.041
AIDS. like everyone else.

506
00:27:13.958 --> 00:27:16.833
Was he your… Were you…

507
00:27:16.916 --> 00:27:17.875
Yeah.

508
00:27:18.833 --> 00:27:20.375
He was the love of my life.

509
00:27:24.916 --> 00:27:26.041
How terrible.

510
00:27:28.833 --> 00:27:29.958
Well…

511
00:27:34.708 --> 00:27:35.625
And you?

512
00:27:39.000 --> 00:27:42.000
Tomorrow. I’m going out with
Santiago Gómez-Arellano.

513
00:27:44.125 --> 00:27:46.916
I hope you have a nice time. But…

514
00:27:48.000 --> 00:27:49.583
You’re not here to talk about him.

515
00:27:49.666 --> 00:27:53.666
You told me there were people
who could surprise you in a good way.

516
00:27:54.541 --> 00:27:55.583
Who were you talking about?

517
00:27:55.666 --> 00:27:57.750
My grandma’s physiotherapist.

518
00:27:58.666 --> 00:27:59.833
What’s up with me?

519
00:28:01.583 --> 00:28:04.000
I’m supposed to
get together with her later.

520
00:28:04.083 --> 00:28:06.750
Have you read <i>Henry and June?</i>

521
00:28:07.333 --> 00:28:09.083
No. Who wrote it?

522
00:28:09.166 --> 00:28:10.458
Anaïs Nin.

523
00:28:11.208 --> 00:28:13.708
A goddess who could write like a demon.

524
00:28:14.208 --> 00:28:17.708
She fucked most of Montparnasse
in the years between the World Wars.

525
00:28:17.791 --> 00:28:19.875
She’s marvelous. I love her.

526
00:28:20.541 --> 00:28:22.708
And you’re gonna love her too. Look.

527
00:28:23.250 --> 00:28:24.291
Read this.

528
00:28:25.750 --> 00:28:29.375
“It’s so beautiful to love
and be free at the same time.”

529
00:28:29.458 --> 00:28:32.875
“It’s so beautiful to love
and be free at the same time.”

530
00:28:36.916 --> 00:28:39.791
But I’m not a French woman
in the '30s in Montparnasse.

531
00:28:40.375 --> 00:28:42.458
I teach Sunday school in Pamplona.

532
00:28:43.916 --> 00:28:47.166
Well. my Sunday school teacher.
don’t you read the book first?

533
00:28:47.666 --> 00:28:49.208
We can talk after that.

534
00:28:50.750 --> 00:28:54.750
When I was 13 years old.
I heard the voice of God speaking to me.

535
00:28:54.833 --> 00:28:56.375
He gave me a mission.

536
00:28:58.166 --> 00:28:59.458
That voice…

537
00:29:00.333 --> 00:29:02.291
came to me around midday…

538
00:29:04.541 --> 00:29:05.958
in the summer…

539
00:29:07.583 --> 00:29:09.375
in my father’s garden.

540
00:29:11.458 --> 00:29:14.708
And after that. I was never alone again.

541
00:29:14.791 --> 00:29:16.250
never helpless.

542
00:29:17.166 --> 00:29:20.208
I have nothing to fear
from mankind’s judgment.

543
00:29:20.291 --> 00:29:25.166
And thus I accept the holy fire
I carry in my soul. and I burn.

544
00:29:26.708 --> 00:29:28.708
Gather all my ashes.

545
00:29:28.791 --> 00:29:32.208
My heart already hears
the voices of the angels.

546
00:29:49.666 --> 00:29:51.125
It was so cool with that lighting…

547
00:29:51.208 --> 00:29:53.625
Hey! Oh my God. you came. sweetie!

548
00:29:53.708 --> 00:29:54.916
I’m thrilled! Did you like it?

549
00:29:55.000 --> 00:29:56.250
- This is the girl.
- Yes.

550
00:29:56.333 --> 00:29:57.583
- You didn’t like it.
- Yes. I did.

551
00:29:57.666 --> 00:29:59.375
- You thought it was garbage.
- No. I loved it.

552
00:29:59.458 --> 00:30:00.291
Really?

553
00:30:00.375 --> 00:30:03.041
Oh. come on now. of course.
she liked it. she loved it.

554
00:30:03.125 --> 00:30:05.625
Just listen to what she’s saying.
Time for a beer. right?

555
00:30:06.666 --> 00:30:07.958
I’m Ane. by the way.

556
00:30:08.791 --> 00:30:09.958
I’m Adela.

557
00:30:10.041 --> 00:30:11.333
Nice to meet you all.

558
00:30:11.416 --> 00:30:12.666
We’ve heard all about you.

559
00:30:12.750 --> 00:30:13.708
Okay then!

560
00:30:13.791 --> 00:30:15.625
Uh… What’s the plan?
Go for drinks? You coming?

561
00:30:15.708 --> 00:30:17.708
- Come on. come on. shots!
- Have one.

562
00:30:17.791 --> 00:30:19.625
I’ll have one. but then I need to go.

563
00:30:19.708 --> 00:30:21.000
- No way. stay!
- C’mon. girl!

564
00:30:21.083 --> 00:30:22.125
Down the hatch. everyone.

565
00:30:22.208 --> 00:30:24.958
One. two. three. woo!

566
00:30:28.250 --> 00:30:29.208
Oh. yeah!

567
00:30:30.291 --> 00:30:32.375
This boy puts up his hand and asks me.

568
00:30:32.958 --> 00:30:36.166
“But when we take communion.
do we have to drink real blood. miss?”

569
00:30:37.375 --> 00:30:40.916
Come on. Javier. you think
that’s real blood? Don’t be stupid.

570
00:30:41.666 --> 00:30:43.708
Well. I didn’t actually say any of that.

571
00:30:43.791 --> 00:30:47.416
I talked about transubstantiation
and the whole works.

572
00:30:47.500 --> 00:30:49.625
But the poor kid was even crying!

573
00:31:06.208 --> 00:31:08.125
- I don’t know the lyrics!
- What?

574
00:31:08.208 --> 00:31:09.583
The lyrics! I don’t know them.

575
00:31:09.666 --> 00:31:10.916
It’s just this!

576
00:31:11.000 --> 00:31:13.000
<i>Sarri. Sarri. Sarri. Sarri. Sarri</i>

577
00:31:16.000 --> 00:31:18.000
<i>Sarri. Sarri. Sarri. Sarri. Sarri…</i>

578
00:31:24.500 --> 00:31:26.000
Yeah! Keep it coming!

579
00:31:47.541 --> 00:31:48.708
Wanna come in?

580
00:32:05.875 --> 00:32:07.416
- Wait here.
- Okay.

581
00:32:15.416 --> 00:32:16.375
Come here.

582
00:32:27.416 --> 00:32:29.875
It’s an anonymous piece
from the early 20th century.

583
00:32:29.958 --> 00:32:30.791
Wow.

584
00:32:30.875 --> 00:32:32.833
It’s in the style of Guido Reni.

585
00:32:33.625 --> 00:32:34.750
It’s beautiful.

586
00:32:36.250 --> 00:32:37.916
You see the clean areas?

587
00:32:38.000 --> 00:32:39.333
Almost the whole face.

588
00:32:43.458 --> 00:32:44.875
And what’s that?

589
00:32:44.958 --> 00:32:46.458
Is it… the real thing?

590
00:32:47.041 --> 00:32:49.500
Yes. they bring them here
to have them restored.

591
00:32:49.583 --> 00:32:51.291
- Really?
- It’s kind of a tradition.

592
00:32:52.416 --> 00:32:54.166
Be careful. They’re fragile.

593
00:32:54.250 --> 00:32:55.208
Okay.

594
00:32:56.500 --> 00:32:57.666
Watch out.

595
00:32:59.833 --> 00:33:02.791
<i>- Doo-doo-doo-doo-doo</i>
- Isabel. please. Isabel. Isabel.

596
00:33:04.375 --> 00:33:06.500
Over here. Please. Isabel. stop.

597
00:33:06.583 --> 00:33:08.625
I’ll give you a thump. my girl!

598
00:33:08.708 --> 00:33:10.750
Okay. take it off now.

599
00:33:12.750 --> 00:33:14.208
That was a blast.

600
00:33:19.041 --> 00:33:19.875
What?

601
00:33:19.958 --> 00:33:23.416
It looks like Lucía got some makeup on you

602
00:33:23.500 --> 00:33:25.416
when she said goodbye.

603
00:33:29.333 --> 00:33:30.625
That looks very nice.

604
00:33:30.708 --> 00:33:32.541
- Oh.
- It suits you.

605
00:33:38.833 --> 00:33:40.875
Oh. that scared me!

606
00:33:44.375 --> 00:33:45.583
It scared me!

607
00:33:54.666 --> 00:33:55.583
Hello?

608
00:33:55.666 --> 00:33:57.875
<i>Adela. what are you doing there so late?</i>

609
00:33:57.958 --> 00:34:00.041
<i>Are you okay? Is something wrong?</i>

610
00:34:00.125 --> 00:34:03.041
Yes. everything’s fine. Dad.
I was just doing some work.

611
00:34:03.125 --> 00:34:05.083
<i>You know who called me?</i>
<i>Jesús. the taxi driver.</i>

612
00:34:05.166 --> 00:34:07.708
- <i>He saw the door was open and got worried.</i>
- I’m going. Bye.

613
00:34:07.791 --> 00:34:09.750
- Wait. Adela. thank you.
<i>- What?</i>

614
00:34:09.833 --> 00:34:10.958
What’s that you said?

615
00:34:11.500 --> 00:34:13.083
<i>Adela? Are you there?</i>

616
00:34:13.166 --> 00:34:14.833
<i>Just come home this minute.</i>

617
00:34:16.833 --> 00:34:19.833
Adela. it’s already
a quarter past twelve. get up.

618
00:34:19.916 --> 00:34:21.666
Santiago is there with your father.

619
00:34:21.750 --> 00:34:23.375
He says you were supposed to meet him.

620
00:34:27.791 --> 00:34:30.000
Now that we’ve had a drink.
I’ll show you something

621
00:34:30.083 --> 00:34:31.708
that’ll blow your mind.

622
00:34:33.750 --> 00:34:34.958
No way!

623
00:34:35.583 --> 00:34:37.458
- How did you even find this?
- Hm?

624
00:34:39.208 --> 00:34:41.041
I did the cover art myself. you know?

625
00:34:41.125 --> 00:34:42.375
That’s amazing.

626
00:34:42.458 --> 00:34:45.375
The Javier Castle pilgrimage. 1988.

627
00:34:45.458 --> 00:34:47.333
Oh. look. That’s Fran…

628
00:34:47.416 --> 00:34:49.750
And the one with the thermos is Maite.

629
00:34:49.833 --> 00:34:51.208
And this guy…

630
00:34:51.291 --> 00:34:52.708
- Him?
- What’s his name again?

631
00:34:53.291 --> 00:34:55.000
Uh. that’s Eusebio. Sebi.

632
00:34:55.083 --> 00:34:56.708
- That’s Sebi. of course!
- That’s right.

633
00:34:57.208 --> 00:34:59.500
- Oh. my God.
- Good times.

634
00:35:00.041 --> 00:35:00.916
Yeah.

635
00:35:01.000 --> 00:35:04.458
You know the image that comes to me
when I remember those days?

636
00:35:06.708 --> 00:35:10.708
You. at night.
holding a hot drink of some sort

637
00:35:11.250 --> 00:35:12.458
in the doorway of the hostel.

638
00:35:12.541 --> 00:35:13.583
Valerian tea.

639
00:35:14.083 --> 00:35:15.875
I still drink it.
My grandma got me into it.

640
00:35:17.333 --> 00:35:18.625
I watched you from the window.

641
00:35:18.708 --> 00:35:21.458
You seemed 20 years older than us.

642
00:35:22.916 --> 00:35:24.166
I was…

643
00:35:25.916 --> 00:35:26.750
What?

644
00:35:27.833 --> 00:35:29.041
Crazy about you.

645
00:35:32.000 --> 00:35:34.583
It would have been very nice
if you’d said so. you know.

646
00:35:35.875 --> 00:35:38.208
I was an idiot. Adela. We all were.

647
00:35:38.791 --> 00:35:39.958
No. Santi.

648
00:35:41.083 --> 00:35:42.291
You were sweet.

649
00:35:56.083 --> 00:35:57.458
Shit. it's raining!

650
00:35:58.125 --> 00:35:59.208
Shit.

651
00:35:59.750 --> 00:36:01.125
Come on! Run. run. run!

652
00:36:02.666 --> 00:36:03.666
Over here!

653
00:36:06.458 --> 00:36:07.333
Ooh.

654
00:36:17.000 --> 00:36:18.375
Adela. I’m nuts about you.

655
00:36:19.833 --> 00:36:21.416
I don’t know if you feel the same.

656
00:36:22.125 --> 00:36:24.500
or if you’re happy about this.
I don’t know anything.

657
00:36:45.833 --> 00:36:46.875
I’m sorry.

658
00:36:48.041 --> 00:36:49.166
I have to go.

659
00:36:52.375 --> 00:36:56.000
AVENIDA SHOPPING MALL

660
00:37:06.250 --> 00:37:08.500
- Merry Christmas. Adela!
- Merry Christmas.

661
00:37:12.750 --> 00:37:14.583
<i>The meat just melts in your mouth.</i>

662
00:37:14.666 --> 00:37:16.666
The butcher always gives me
the best pieces.

663
00:37:16.750 --> 00:37:18.541
- This is just delicious.
- Very good.

664
00:37:18.625 --> 00:37:20.500
What’s in store for us at Mass. I wonder?

665
00:37:20.583 --> 00:37:22.333
It’s the first one
from this priest. you know.

666
00:37:22.416 --> 00:37:24.958
He’ll give communion with a limp wrist.

667
00:37:25.041 --> 00:37:27.250
How on earth did that man
get assigned to our church?

668
00:37:27.333 --> 00:37:29.583
- A charming gift from the archbishop.
- Right.

669
00:37:37.666 --> 00:37:39.041
Honey. we were joking.

670
00:37:40.208 --> 00:37:41.625
I don’t think it was funny.

671
00:37:43.416 --> 00:37:44.833
That’s okay. I’ll do the rest.

672
00:37:45.500 --> 00:37:46.458
I’ll finish up.

673
00:37:47.083 --> 00:37:48.333
You can dry.

674
00:37:54.083 --> 00:37:55.083
Adela.

675
00:37:55.583 --> 00:37:58.541
I know that we’ve been on edge lately.

676
00:37:58.625 --> 00:38:01.416
But I’m just so scared
that someone will hurt you.

677
00:38:02.166 --> 00:38:03.375
I’m worried sick.

678
00:38:10.416 --> 00:38:11.500
There.

679
00:38:11.583 --> 00:38:14.208
Mom. I need to see a gynecologist.

680
00:38:16.375 --> 00:38:18.041
Darling. another time.

681
00:38:19.916 --> 00:38:21.416
Leave it. I’ll take care of it.

682
00:38:25.833 --> 00:38:27.000
Do as you wish.

683
00:38:29.083 --> 00:38:30.916
“When my spirit faints within me.

684
00:38:31.000 --> 00:38:33.000
it is You who watch over my way."

685
00:38:33.541 --> 00:38:37.041
"There is no one at my right hand
who is concerned for me."

686
00:38:37.125 --> 00:38:38.708
"No refuge can be found for me."

687
00:38:39.250 --> 00:38:41.583
"To no one does it matter
whether I live or die."

688
00:38:43.041 --> 00:38:45.000
"Thus I cry out to you. O Lord."

689
00:38:46.000 --> 00:38:50.375
"Deliver me from my persecutors
for they are stronger than I.”

690
00:38:58.708 --> 00:39:00.125
<i>"Merry Christmas. sweetie."</i>

691
00:39:00.208 --> 00:39:03.416
<i>"On New Year’s Eve we’re going to the bar.</i>
<i>We’re gonna wear costumes."</i>

692
00:39:04.166 --> 00:39:05.083
<i>"You up for it?"</i>

693
00:39:05.666 --> 00:39:07.041
<i>"I really wanna see you."</i>

694
00:39:07.125 --> 00:39:08.208
<i>"Isabel."</i>

695
00:39:09.333 --> 00:39:10.416
<i>Good morning!</i>

696
00:39:10.500 --> 00:39:14.291
<i>It’s just a matter of hours</i>
<i>before we say goodbye to 1999.</i>

697
00:39:14.375 --> 00:39:16.000
<i>Tonight. we enter the new millennium</i>

698
00:39:16.083 --> 00:39:20.541
<i>and we finally find out what happens</i>
<i>with the famous Y2K bug.</i>

699
00:39:31.583 --> 00:39:33.333
Ah. shit.

700
00:39:41.333 --> 00:39:43.333
- Hello?
<i>- Adela. it’s José.</i>

701
00:39:43.833 --> 00:39:44.958
<i>I need to see you.</i>

702
00:39:47.625 --> 00:39:48.750
Come with me.

703
00:39:50.083 --> 00:39:52.541
But where are we going?
I have to go home for dinner.

704
00:39:52.625 --> 00:39:53.916
Sure. Just come.

705
00:39:59.375 --> 00:40:01.916
Honey. you’re drunk.
and the night hasn’t even started.

706
00:40:02.750 --> 00:40:05.666
When the loneliness
gets to me. I come here. I sit down.

707
00:40:05.750 --> 00:40:06.791
and I watch them.

708
00:40:08.041 --> 00:40:09.625
I don’t ever go in. of course.

709
00:40:10.208 --> 00:40:12.083
But it makes me feel good.

710
00:40:12.791 --> 00:40:15.416
It’s like I’m introducing you
to my family. you know?

711
00:40:16.541 --> 00:40:17.666
They look happy.

712
00:40:17.750 --> 00:40:20.041
They are happy right now. for sure.

713
00:40:20.125 --> 00:40:23.833
When you get to a place
that feels like your own. really yours.

714
00:40:25.000 --> 00:40:27.708
with people who understand you.
nothing’s better than that.

715
00:40:31.291 --> 00:40:32.333
What is it?

716
00:40:33.250 --> 00:40:34.958
I kissed Santiago.

717
00:40:35.041 --> 00:40:36.041
Hmm.

718
00:40:38.041 --> 00:40:39.250
I liked it very much.

719
00:40:39.916 --> 00:40:43.041
It was great. But. as soon
as I closed my eyes.

720
00:40:43.125 --> 00:40:46.041
the only face I could see
in my head was hers.

721
00:40:46.125 --> 00:40:48.166
The masseuse with the big personality?

722
00:40:48.875 --> 00:40:50.083
Yes. Isabel.

723
00:40:53.541 --> 00:40:55.916
When I’m with Santiago…

724
00:40:57.333 --> 00:40:58.666
I feel attractive.

725
00:41:00.041 --> 00:41:01.666
But when I’m with Isabel.

726
00:41:02.500 --> 00:41:03.750
I feel so free.

727
00:41:05.125 --> 00:41:07.416
It’s a totally new experience.

728
00:41:08.583 --> 00:41:10.000
I’ve always tried to…

729
00:41:10.583 --> 00:41:12.375
be invisible. José.

730
00:41:13.041 --> 00:41:14.708
Shut out the whole world.

731
00:41:15.541 --> 00:41:17.583
I was numb about all of it.

732
00:41:17.666 --> 00:41:18.958
My own body.

733
00:41:19.041 --> 00:41:21.208
my… my infertility.

734
00:41:21.291 --> 00:41:22.375
the medication.

